{"id":479,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":479,"title":"Eve","subtitle":"","short_title":"Eve","uri":"/scriptures/bd/eve","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/eve.t1","order":".000.1228"},[".title","Eve"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/eve.p1","order":".000.1229"},"The name given in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/2.21-22"},"Gen. 2:21–22"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/3.20"},"3:20"],"to the first woman; see also",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/3"},"Gen. 3"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/4.1"},"4:1"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/2-cor/11.3"},"2 Cor. 11:3"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/1-tim/2.13"},"1 Tim. 2:13"],". The name means “the mother of all living” (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/4.26"},"Moses 4:26"],"; see also",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/5.11"},"1 Ne. 5:11"],"). She was the wife of Adam and will share eternal glory with him. Eve’s recognition of the necessity of the Fall and the joys of Redemption is recorded in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/5.11"},"Moses 5:11"],". Latter-day revelation confirms the biblical account of Eve and gives us an awareness of her nobility."]]],"refs":null}
